Process Safety Engineer

Thatcher Company

- Salt Lake City, UT 84104 (Glendale area)

Thatcher Company is a diversified chemical manufacturer, re-packager and distributor headquartered in Salt Lake City, Utah. The company was founded in 1967 and has grown to be a major chemical supplier and distributor in the United States. Thatcher’s diversification, coupled with ever broadening product offerings, allows us to respond to the changing needs of our customers and the marketplace. Our core values include integrity, employee success, win-win relationships, customer focus, stability, safety & environment, and continuous improvement.
Thatcher Company is seeking an experienced Process Safety Engineer to join our growing team! This is a long-term position requiring a higher level of thinking and is designed to help an individual grow, develop and take on more skills within the organization. The position will be responsible for implementing and supporting process safety regulations such as OSHA's PSM Program and creating training courses as SOP’s are developed.
Required Qualifications
BS degree in Engineering (Chemical preferred) with 5 years’ experience
Some familiarity with safety regulations (PSM, RMP etc.)
Some familiarity with industrial codes/standards (NFPA, ICC etc.)
AutoCAD LT skills or the ability to learn
Analytical thinker with interpersonal skills
Ability to see the 'big picture' and skills to motivate others towards that picture
Not afraid of change, willingness to modify programs as better ideas are proposed
Take constructive criticism and use it to improve existing programs
Strong work ethic and desire to strive for continuous improvement
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Major Accountabilities
Assist in the development of all Process Safety Information (P&ID's, PFD's, Process Chemistry etc.)
Assist in preparation of PHA's and participate in HAZOP's
Work with Operations and Maintenance to develop and improve SOP's
Coordinate mechanical integrity inspections with contactors
Manage the CMMS/EAM for equipment and preventative maintenance accuracy
Manage the training software program and assist in the development and improvement of the employee training program
Assist engineering in correctly completing MOC and PSSR paperwork
Participate and lead compliance audits
Manage the Action Tracking database
Support the project and process engineers in helping drive PSM recommendations to completion
Develop metrics and reports
What’s In It for You?
Competitive salary (DOE and Skill Level)
Benefit package includes health, dental, and life insurance.
Paid vacation, holidays and sick leave.
Retirement plan is 100% employer paid. It is significant.
MUST BE U.S. CITIZEN OR HAVE PERMANENT RESIDENT STATUS
Job Type: Full-time
Salary: $21.00 to $29.00 /hour
